### Enhanced Path Alias System (Best Practice âœ…)

**Problem**: Using ugly relative paths like `"../../../../prisma/generated/client"` and limited alias organization
**Solution**: Implemented comprehensive path alias system following Next.js best practices:

#### Path Alias Configuration (tsconfig.json)

```json
{
  "compilerOptions": {
    "baseUrl": ".",
    "paths": {
      "@/*": ["./src/*"],
      "@/components/*": ["./src/components/*"],
      "@/lib/*": ["./src/lib/*"],
      "@/app/*": ["./src/app/*"],
      "@/ui/*": ["./src/components/ui/*"],
      "#/*": ["./"],
      "#root/*": ["./"],
      "#prisma/*": ["./prisma/*"],
      "#prisma": ["./prisma/generated/client"],
      "#public/*": ["./public/*"]
    }
  }
}
```

#### Alias Usage Patterns

**Source Code Aliases (@ prefix):**

- `@/*` â†’ General src folder access
- `@/components/*` â†’ React components
- `@/lib/*` â†’ Utilities and shared code
- `@/app/*` â†’ Next.js app directory
- `@/ui/*` â†’ shadcn/ui components

**Root Folder Aliases (# prefix):**

- `#/*` â†’ Root directory access
- `#prisma` â†’ Prisma client (clean access)
- `#prisma/*` â†’ Prisma folder contents
- `#public/*` â†’ Public assets

